descript.abstract: Parcel polygon layer for Morro Bay watershed from Morro Bay National Estuary Program. Manual updates to parcels boundaries were made in accordance with 2014 data from the San Luis Obispo County Assessor's Office.id = code assigned to parcels for purpose of Marxan (1-670)Area = units are square feetAPN = Assessor's Parcel Number, a standardized number by county for cataloguing parcels
descript.purpose: Provide a seemless county-wide layer for San Luis Obispo County GIS users
descript.supplinf: 120,307 Parcels, not including the condo layers, attributed with APN's

cntorgp.cntorg: REQUIRED: The organization responsible for the metadata information.
cntorgp.cntper: REQUIRED: The person responsible for the metadata information.

cntaddr.addrtype: REQUIRED: The mailing and/or physical address for the organization or individual.
cntaddr.city: REQUIRED: The city of the address.
cntaddr.state: REQUIRED: The state or province of the address.
cntaddr.postal: REQUIRED: The ZIP or other postal code of the address.

cntinfo.cntvoice: REQUIRED: The telephone number by which individuals can speak to the organization or individual.

metainfo.metstdn: FGDC Content Standards for Digital Geospatial Metadata

dataIdInfo.idPurp: Provide a seemless county-wide layer for San Luis Obispo County GIS users
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Parcel polygon layer for Morro Bay watershed from Morro Bay National Estuary Program. Manual updates to parcels boundaries were made in accordance with 2014 data from the San Luis Obispo County Assessor's Office.

id = code assigned to parcels for purpose of Marxan (1-670)

Area = units are square feet

APN = Assessor's Parcel Number, a standardized number by county for cataloguing parcels

FID_riverb = distinguishes riparian parcels from non-riparian parcels. -1 = non-riparian, 0 = riparian

LUC = land use category, PF= public facility, OS= open space, AG= agriculture. RR= rural residential, RS= rural suburban, REC = recreational, RSF= Residential Single Family, CR = commercial retail, RL = rural lands
